s alongside the biblical God, who at first presents himself as the liberator of the oppressed but ends up a cruel ruler who delights in the infliction of suffering on his friends and enemies alike. In other words, this is the story of how God becomes the devil-a devil who remains with us in our ostensibly secular age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDevilxChristianityxHistory of doctrines. 0aGood and evilxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 4aAnselm of Canterbury. 4aChristian theology. 4aGiorgio Agamben. 4aHebrew Bible. 4aSatan. 4aapocalyptic. 4adevil. 4aeschatology. 4apolitical theology. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360021840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503600218423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503600218.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles